of Motion Hearing before the Honorable David M. Reddy on March 3, 2016
Court Reporter: Linda C. Matoska
Order Denying Motion to Suppress

3:05 pm  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given. 
Atty Andrew Herrmann appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deft Jeffrey R. Webber in court with attorney John Dade.  
Matter is before the Court on the Deft's Motion to Dismiss.  
3:05 pm  Officer Jeffrey Price is sworn and testifies on direct exam of Atty Herrmann.  
Atty Herrmann makes a record as to other people currently in the courtroom and asks that they be excluded.  
Response by Atty Dade.  There are potential witnesses in the Courtroom.  Atty Dade has instructed them not to discuss the case.  
Court excludes witnesses from the Courtroom.  
3:14 pm  Cross exam by Atty Dade.  
Exhibit #1 is marked and identified as a portion of Officer Webber's testimony from the prelim. 
3:41 pm  Redirect by Atty Herrmann.  
3:43 pm  Recross by Atty Dade.  
3:45 pm  Redirect by Atty Herrmann.  
3:45 pm  Recross by Atty Dade.  
3:45 pm  Witness excused.  Attorney Dade is not moving Exhibit #1 into evidence.  
Randall Andrews is Atty Dade's next witness.  Atty Herrmann objects to this witness being called because he is a co-actor and is represented by Counsel.
Response by Atty Dade.  
Response by Atty Herrmann.  
Court agrees and does not believe Mr. Andrews should be called without his Atty being present.  
3:48 pm  Court takes a short recess to allow Atty Dade to try to contact Atty Kramer.  
3:49 pm  Atty Herrmann speaks with Atty Kramer on Atty Dade's cell phone.  
3:49 pm  Court takes short recess and asks that Atty Kramer call the Courtroom and be put on speaker phone to make a record.  
3:56 pm  Atty Stephen Kramer is now appearing by TELEPHONE.  
3:56 pm  Atty Kramer makes a record as to his discussions with Atty Dade as to what questions would be asked of Mr. Andrews.  
Atty Kramer indicates he is in his office and can be in Court in approximately 10 minutes.  
3:59 pm  Alexis Montalto is sworn and testifies on exam of Atty Dade.  
4:07 pm  Cross exam by Atty Herrmann.  
4:08 pm  Redirect by Atty Herrmann.  
4:08 pm  Witness excused.  
4:19 pm  Court in session.  Atty Kramer is present in Court and makes a record as to his concerns as to what Atty Herrmann will ask his client.  Court doesn't feel it can limit Atty Herrmann's questions.  Response by Atty Dade.  Court notes it cannot overrule an objection to a question that has not been asked.  Response by Atty Herrmann.  
4:23 pm  Jeffrey Webber is sworn and testifies on direct exam of Atty Dade.  
4:28 pm  Cross exam by Atty Herrmann.  
4:32 pm  Witness excused.  
4:33 pm  Officer Price returns to witness stand, acknowledges he is still under oath and testifies on exam of Atty Dade.  
4:33 pm  Officer Price testifies on exam of Atty Herrmann.  
4:33 pm  Response by Officer Price to Court's questions.  
4:36 pm  Further questions of Officer Price by Atty Dade.  
4:37 pm  Testimony concluded.  Argument by Atty Herrmann.  
4:41 pm  Argument by Atty Dade.  
4:51 pm  Court makes findings and denies the Motion to Suppress for the reason set forth on the record.  
4:57 pm  Discussion as to the number of prior convictions for Mr. Webber, if any.    
This file will track the deft's other pending case (2015CF000391) which is currently scheduled for FPT and JT.  
4:59 pm  Court in recess.  Status conference scheduled for May 11, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
